# Transcribed from cf16_2.main.cpp: five add_edge batches driving the
# symmetric-pair join. Symmetry of 1<->2 is broken (batch 3) and restored
# (batch 4); the 5,5 self-loop and the 3<->4 pair are removed. Final
# symmetric = {(1,2),(2,1)}. The driver's six interleaved cursor dumps
# (mid-run flip-flops) are not expressible in a final-state sidecar.
batch
+ add_edge 1 2
+ add_edge 2 1
+ add_edge 3 4
end
# completes (3,4)/(4,3); self-loop
batch
+ add_edge 4 3
+ add_edge 5 5
end
# breaks symmetry of 1<->2
batch
- add_edge 2 1
end
# restore one, remove self-loop
batch
+ add_edge 2 1
- add_edge 5 5
end
# remove both directions of 3<->4
batch
- add_edge 3 4
- add_edge 4 3
end
